From: Ian Rogers <irogers@google.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Oct 2025 10:58:38 -0700
Subject: perf metricgroup: Missed free on error path
Git-commit: 3bae9228a5503f7fb6464e895c3f542221ce9395
Patch-mainline: v6.19-rc1
References: perf-sle16.1-v6.19-userspace-update

If an out-of-memory occurs the expr also needs freeing.

Signed-off-by: Ian Rogers <irogers@google.com>
Signed-off-by: Namhyung Kim <namhyung@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Tony Jones <tonyj@suse.de>
---
 tools/perf/util/metricgroup.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/tools/perf/util/metricgroup.c b/tools/perf/util/metricgroup.c
index 595b83142d2c..c822cf5da53b 100644
--- a/tools/perf/util/metricgroup.c
+++ b/tools/perf/util/metricgroup.c
@@ -1455,6 +1455,7 @@ static int parse_groups(struct evlist *perf_evlist,
 
 		if (!expr->metric_name) {
 			ret = -ENOMEM;
+			free(expr);
 			free(metric_events);
 			goto out;
 		}

